<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the western Brisbane family market in detail. Mount Ommaney's buyers are upgraders and established families: they have equity, they know exactly what they want, and they compare your home directly against Jindalee, Westlake and Riverhills at comparable price points. The campaign needs to frame your property's specific advantages clearly, because this buyer has done their homework before they ever walk through the door.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Mount Ommaney Centre gives the suburb a strong retail anchor that sets it apart from Riverhills and Jindalee. Families who want to be walking distance from supermarkets, medical centres and specialty retail consistently target this suburb over its neighbours. Blocks backing onto or with views of the western Brisbane greenspace network attract a clear premium, and homes along the elevated ridgeline streets command stronger prices from buyers who specifically want that outlook and aspect. The Centenary Motorway provides a direct CBD commute, and that combination of retail proximity, greenspace amenity and motorway access makes Mount Ommaney one of the west's most self-contained suburban addresses.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
